A vintage-style illustration depicting a small, humble stone chapel from antiquity gradually transforming and morphing into a massive gleaming corporate skyscraper as it stretches from left to right across the canvas. The left side shows weathered ancient Mediterranean architecture with simple wooden doors and olive trees, rendered in warm sepia and ochre tones. As the structure progresses rightward, it gradually incorporates Roman columns, then Gothic European spires, finally culminating in a towering glass-and-steel American megastructure with spotlights beaming into a dramatic sunset sky. The transition is seamless and organic, like geological strata compressed into one building. Golden coins and dollar bills subtly swirl in the wind around the modern portion. The overall mood is contemplative and slightly melancholic, with rich amber lighting reminiscent of aged photographs and classical oil paintings from the 1920s magazine illustration era.
